You Know You're Addicted to Dragonball Z When...
You can recite every word of the original Japanese DBZ episodes/movies by heart. You claim to be an expert on the Japanese language, then get kicked out of Japan on your vacation because all you knew how to do was insult people. You scream, beg, whine, plead for your parents to order the (expensive!!) Dragon Ball Z games for your Playstation, then when all else fails you threaten to do a Big Bang and blow up the planet. You're convinced the Dragon Balls DO exist, and you begin saving up your allowance to go on a quest to find them. You stand outside screaming "NIMBUS!!" at night (after all, you wouldn't want to embarass your parents by doing it during the day, would you?) You instantly pummel ANYONE who says Vegeta has a receeding hairline. You take a martial arts class and ask the instructor when Gregory andd Bubbles will be arriving, then pout and demand to speak to King Ki. You check every morining to see if you've sprouted a tail. You buy a plastic toy sword, strap it to your back, and tell anyone who asks that Tabion the Brave gave it to you, then look at them like they're crazy when they ask who that is. You freak out when you have chicken-pox / measels because you think that all that pink skin means you're turning into Frieza. You suddenly become a vegetarian and eat nothing but carrots, rice, and other vegetables. You secretly try to grow Senzu Beans and believe you are succeeding. You ended up in the hospital because you severely injured your muscles trying to do a Ginyu pose. You make yourself a perfect replica of Saiyan armour for Halloween.....then refuse to take it off. You've actually convinced your friends that you met the Dragon Ball Gang last night for drinks. You name your cat Karin, and nod wisely whenever it meows at you. You've almost popped a vein in your forehead trying to will yourself to fly. You learned to use a computer just so you could look at all those neat DBZ pictures. You then refer to your computer desk as you "Capsule Corp. Lab". You go outside at night, stare longingly at the stars, and sing; Someday My Princce Will Come. You know that Vegeta and all the other DBZ characters would find you supremely cool and want to hang out with you. You refuse you go near your freezer. You refer to your mom as Chichi (when she isn't within earshot). You're famous throughout your city for the time when you actually tried to stop a bank robbery with your Kamehameha (and maybe your actually succeeded!) You failed biology class because of your diagram of a Cell. Whenever there's a severe storm, you nod wisely and say, "Someone's calling the Dragon...." You can actually spout off a surprising number of phrases in Japanese. You've gotten up a five a.m. every morning just to watch the replay of the DBZ episode that was on yesterday....even though you already saw it ten times! During full moons you stand outside screaming until you pass out. Even if you're in high school and you're a girl, your parents still shop for your birthday and Christmas presents in the same aisle that they shop in for your little eight-year-old brother....the action figure aisle. You took home ec. class because you were determined to become a better cook than Chichi. You took sewing class to learn how to make a cuddly little Vegeta plush toy. You blast down anyone who insults your Saiyan pride. When you laugh, you say, "Kameha-ha-ha-ha!" You burst into tears when a character, ANY character dies, regardless of Dragon Ball Availability You almost drowned because you stood in the path of an approaching tidal wave, convinced that your Genki Dama summouned it to you You giggle hysterically when you're told to eat your vegetables. You begged, pleaded, bribed, and finally beat the crap out of your younger brother for his Burger King Piccolo DBZ toy, and you don't even LIKE Piccolo You lose sleep over wondering about Frieza's sexual orientation, possibly due to nightmares You *try* to wrap yourself around your computer, purring contentedly whenever a dbz related download finishes Your thumbs are sore, cracked, and bleeding but you finally managed to beat DB Ultimate Battle 22 without dying ONCE! You attacked the guy at the hardware store who looks like Nappa and almost gave him a concussion in your excitement to demand where Vegeta was You've gotten kicked out of church for standing up in the middle of a funeral and yelling "HEY!!! LET'S JUST GO GET THE DRAGON BALLS!!" You're convinced that Japan actually has a secret fourth DB series, and they just aren't sharing You're ALSO convinced that you hold the potential to create another DB series if only Toriyama would return your phone calls You went into shock when they introduced Frieza's family, then immediately began putting in calls to Jerry Springer about lipstick wearing midgets with english, uncaring giant fathers You're almost convinced yourself your toaster could POSSIBLY have been made by Dr Gero and therefore has android possibility Deathly sick and exhausted, you STILL managed to chase down, in the rain, after four hours the dog who ran off with your Kuririn action figure You spend hours making a power pole in your woodshop class You watch the weather channel for signs of nimbuses You believe it's possible to focus your ki into a deadly blast if you really wanted to, but are just too exhausted from all the "Powering Up And Customary Screaming" you've done that day You made little score cards to hold up during the fight scenes You try to fuse with your friends. You try to shoot your teacher with a Big Bang Attack. You jump off of buildings and try to fly. You eat rice every night...at a mad speed. You test your powers out on your little sister. You dress in red pants with an red shirt every day. You dye your hair yellow and claim your Super Saiyan. You scream at people you don't like and then try to blast them. You only answer to the DBZ name of your choice. You hate Dende. You spend hours try ing to use the "instant transmission" and only end up with two finger prints on your forehead. You strap a piece of colored glass over you left eye and laugh at everyone, telling them what pathetic power levels they have. You start wearing weighted clothing in order to increase you power level. You plan to name your son Gohan. You plan to name your daughter Pan. You throw fisbees at people and yell "distructo disc." You draw a "third" eye on your forehead. You shave your head and put six little dots on your forehead. You spike your hair and dye it yellow. You go to the zoo and yell insults at all the monkeys. When you have a problem you think "what would Goku (Gohan, Vegita...) do." You actually get these jokes and pass them on to other friends who are addicted to Dragonball Z.

Well, if you haven't heard already, we had a bomb threat here on campus today. BUT NO...WAIT...IT GETS BETTER!!
It just HAD to be outside of MY dorm (Smith Hall)  I was heading out to go to my ANT 2511 lecture at the stadium.  
Class starts at 11:15 and it's huge so I normally leave at 10:45 so I can get a good seat. (Yes Momma, I sit upfront 
in all my classes ^_^)  Anyway, I walked out the side door and got a glimpse of something blinking in different colors.
Cop cars, can everyone say "yay"?  Well, I saw Jonathan (a fellow flute player in Marching Chiefs) and went to ask him what was up.  He said no one really knew at that time but it seemed like some idiot pulled a gun or a bomb had been reported.  My guess was bomb since an officer started takeing police tape and wrapping it around the area.  He also said we were too close.  Too close was apparently a building away. So anywho, I head on to my class. To my dismay, I had to take a detour through the track.  Lucky for me, it had an open gate in the direction that I was headed.  I get to class, class goes on, I get extra credit (yay!), and class ends.  I was heading back to my hall for a nap and I saw that the firetruck I had passed earlier was still there....and they were still blocking roads.  Fun Fun.  I walked up to some people directing traffic.  They told me I had to go around again unless I wanted to stick around and help them tell people to not go through there.  I declined and took the track route again....unfortunetly I forgot where the opening in the gate was so I had to hop the fence....with a backpack and other school items. FUN FUN.  I eventually made it up to Salley (which is right next to Smith)  THE WHOLE AREA was taped off!!  My building had also been evacuated.  I took the long way behind Salley and went to the back of Smith where my fellow hall mates were.  I sat around for 30 minutes with Alyssa and her roomie before they let us back in.  No bombs went off.  There probably wasn't even a bomb.  Several students suspect that some group of people had plotted to get out of a test by pulling off this sceme.  A couple of classes were indeed cancelled.  It took 2 hours and 30 minutes for them to clear the area.  So there's my exciting day on campus.  Yay, flashing lights galore!

Ok, everyone knows I tried out for the Marching Chiefs.  For those of you that haven't heard, I made Glue Crew.  I still get to play in the stands, but I don't march.  I set up the ladders and what not for the drum majors during halftime.  

Some interesting things have happened while I have been up here.  Saturday night I was going to go to the Student Life Building with Nick, Rocky, and Anna to see Monty Python and the Holy Grail.  Yes, I've seen the movie, but never on the big screen.  We were going to meet Anna at the SLB because she was at another movie...I think Kill Bill 2.  

Anyway, Nick goes upstairs to get Rocky out of his cave and into society.  Rocky wants to take his Motorcycle, which is known to be a piece of crap.  He cranks it so it'll warm up.  Finally we are on our way to the movie.  
	
About a block away from Conradi Nick and I notice that Rocky has pulled off the road into the median.  We find a place to turn around and head back to see what's up. Rocky's bike had run out of gas.  It wasn't like we could tow his bike or anything, but we could help him push the stupid thing back to the apartment.  I mean, come on...it's all uphill and Rocky's not exactly physically fit.  Nick and I drive back to the apartment and walk back to help Rocky.  He's managed to get pretty far on his own, so we just keep him company.  Of course we weren't going to miss the opportunity to rag on him about the gas and making us miss the movie.  We get his bike back to the apartment complex and we all hop in the jeep to go get gas.  Our plan is to go to the gas station up the street,buy a gas can, buy gas to put in the can, and then come home.  Simple right? HA! In a perfect world maybe..
	
So we go to the gas station and Rocky goes in.  Two minutes later he is back out because they don't sell gas cans.  You would THINK that a GAS STATION would sell GAS CANS!  But NOOOOOO, not in Tallahassee apparently.  So we go to about three or four more gas stations and get the same result.  As scary as it seems, Rocky and I were both on the same wave length.  We brought the fact that Walmart sells everything to Nick's attention.  Nick does NOT want to go back to Walmart.  He and I have been there WAY too often since we got up here last week. To his dismay, no other gas stations were open, so we were forced to go to Walmart.  
	
We get into the parking lot and Nick parks by the one door that was CLOSED for the night. (You know how they only leave one door open after about 10:00...well this was after 12:00)  I told Nick and Rocky that that entrance was closed, but did they listen? Nope.  Go figure, right?  So we make it to the other entrance and have to walk back the way we came inside the building because the Auto Department is on the opposite wall than the one beside the open doors.  
	
Nick and I tell Rocky that we'll be on the isle with the Snow Cone stuff.  We even pointed to the isle. Then we would come back to the auto stuff.  Rocky says ok and heads to the gas cans.  Nick and I took our time picking out a new snow cone flavor and then headed back to the tools and junk.  
	
We went up and down the isles looking for any sign of Rocky or gas cans. We found the latter. We head back to the front of the store to look for Rocky.  Of course, he's not there.  *rolls eyes*  We stand around waiting for him for a few minutes.  It's getting late and we're getting bored, so we start walking to the customer service desk with the plan to page him, wait no more than five minutes, and then leave him if he doesn't show up. We intersect him before we got to the service desk.  Darnit right?  
	
The three of us go to check out our stuff and I get a look at the casher.  It looks like a man.  It was over-weight with the figure of a man, looked rather butch, and had a curly MULLET!! NOOOOOO!!!! However,the it was NOT a man, but yet a woman.  That poor thing. :o( 
	
The girl that the casher was checking out had a handful of items, one of the items being spray paint.  The casher had to card the girl for the spray paint.  What is the world coming to these days?!  Then, once everything was scanned, the girl went to pay with her FSU Card (it works like a Check Card/Debt Card).  BUT NO! She couldn't because Suntrust does all of their upgrades at random times on Saturday nights. WHY SATURDAY NIGHTS is beyond me.  I mean, come on!  That's when all the FSU students are out and about!  The girl has no other means of payment on her, so she asks if she needs to go get cash from her friend outside.  As soon as those words came out of her mouth, my mind screamed NO HON, They'll let you come back tomorrow to pay for your stuff.  Here's your sign!  But good for me, I didn't say anything. 
	
Without further delay, my group and I checked out.  We got back in the jeep.  Nick driving, Rocky in the passenger seat, and me behind Rocky. Rocky is fiddling with the gas can, trying to figure out how it opens and what not.  He flips down the sun visor looking for one of those lighted mirrors.  Not finding one, he rants to Nick about how his Jeep is lame.  I roll my eyes and hit the button above Rocky's head that turns on the Map Light.  I proceed to make fun of him for a minute.  We finally pull into a gas station and Rocky STILL hasn't figured out the gas can.  Nick makes fun of Rocky and then starts helping him.  For the next few minutes, they are BOTH trying to figure out how the nozzle goes on the can.  Ah yes, the many adventures of Nick and Rocky.  Nick finally figures it out and Rocky goes and gets his gas.  We go back to Conradi afterward and part ways.  Nick and I don't want to hang out for Rocky's trip to the store to get more gas.  

That concludes the hour long hunt for a gas can. *sigh*  For those of you who are wondering about poor Anna, Nick called her before we walked to help Rocky.

There are more stories to tell, but my time is limited in between classes.  You'll just have to wait until I get more free time.

MEG ^_^
